OL,3,CGuernsey's health service will be
OL,4,C'overwhelmed' unless focus changes
OL,6,FDr Brink explains: "Quite simply if we
OL,7,Fdo nothing, our health and care
OL,8,Fservices will become overwhelmed in 20
OL,9,Fyears time and we'll have to make
OL,10,Fimpossibly difficult choices about who
OL,11,Fgets treated.
OL,13,F"We'll also have new treatments
OL,14,Femerging so what you're looking at is
OL,15,Fa perfect storm with an increased
OL,16,Fdemand on the health and care services.
OL,18,F"We feel we can moderate that demand
OL,19,Fif we put appropriate services in
OL,20,Fplace."
