OL,3,CGuernsey's health service will be
OL,4,C'overwhelmed' unless focus changes
OL,6,F"If somebody is healthy and well, not
OL,7,Fonly is it good for that individual
OL,8,Fthemselves, but it's also good for the
OL,9,Feconomy. They're more likely to be
OL,10,Fworking.
OL,12,F"It's good for the wider island.
OL,13,FThey're more likely to volunteer, be
OL,14,Finvolved in caring activities and so
OL,15,Fon. So having a healthy population
OL,16,Fmakes economic good sense."
